# AI Assistant Rules for Automate Faceless Content Project

Whenever you add new code or make significant changes to this project, you MUST follow this A-Z automated workflow to ensure code quality and deployment:

## 1. CHECK & FIX (A-Z Check)
- Always review your code for syntax errors and logic bugs before finalizing.
- Run `npm run build` to verify that the VitePress site builds successfully without any errors.
- If there are errors, FIX them immediately until the build passes.

## 2. PASS & INSTALL
- Ensure all tests and builds pass.
- If new dependencies were added, run `npm install` to update the `package-lock.json` and ensure everything is correctly linked.

## 3. UP GITHUB
- Use `git status` to check changed files.
- Stage changes using `git add .`
- Commit changes with a descriptive message: `git commit -m "feat/fix: description"`
- Push the code to the repository: `git push origin main`

## 4. DEPLOY CLOUDFLARE PAGE
- Cloudflare Pages is typically configured to auto-deploy upon a `git push` to the `main` branch.
- If manual deployment is required via CLI, run:
  `npx wrangler pages deploy .vitepress/dist --project-name automate-faceless-content`
  
Always remind the user when you are executing these deployment steps.
